comment: Factory class for creating integrity formulas based on the app being installed.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula packageNameEquals(@NonNull String packageName)
methods.comment: Returns an integrity formula that checks the equality to a package name.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula certificatesContain(@NonNull String appCertificate)
methods.comment:
* Returns an integrity formula that checks if the app certificates contain {@code
         * appCertificate}.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula versionCodeEquals(@NonNull long versionCode)
methods.comment: Returns an integrity formula that checks the equality to a version code.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula versionCodeGreaterThan(@NonNull long versionCode)
methods.comment:
* Returns an integrity formula that checks the app's version code is greater than the
         * provided value.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula versionCodeGreaterThanOrEqualTo(@NonNull long versionCode)
methods.comment:
* Returns an integrity formula that checks the app's version code is greater than or equal
         * to the provided value.

methods.name: public static IntegrityFormula isPreInstalled()
methods.comment: Returns an integrity formula that is valid when app is pre-installed.

public static IntegrityFormula versionCodeEquals(@NonNull long versionCode)

public static IntegrityFormula versionCodeGreaterThanOrEqualTo(@NonNull long versionCode)
